This paper discusses the technologies that are driving the evolution of communication networks towards 5G, which is a topic that falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the architecture of 5G networks, which involves the use of virtualization and software-defined networking, which are topics that fall under the categories of Information Theory (cs.IT), Communications (cs.COMM), Architecture (cs.AR), and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
